			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I did a task last night (the Sentry one mentioned previously).  While in Veksar I ran into another bard that was doing the same quest.  Curious to see what would happen if we fought the same mob, we discovered that if grouped everyone that needs the mob to complete a task gets credit for every kill.  In other words, if everyone in the group gets the same task, then killing the mobs (in my case 10 Sentries) will complete the task for everyone.  Needless to say, we cut through the task fairly quickly once we duoed.  No more than an hour.  I ended up getting about half a yellow in an AA from the fighting and another yellow from completing the task.
<br />

<br />
Not the best exps for a full group but is you wanted to do something while waiting for a raid, then it is pretty easy to knock one out.</span></td>
