				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Tasks don't even waste your time<a name="62039"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 15 04 9:07 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The hook may be the value for the under 50, or under 40 crowd. Lets hope so, although most soloable classes can do 12% exp in 15 minutes (at level 23) as well. I am guessing the cash reward was about what a fine steel weapon is worth, if that?
<br />

<br />
 2-4% exp for a lvl 65 for 2 hours and 138 pp (maye another 80 or so from mobs) is an absolute total waste.
<br />

<br />
It is not very soloable. Going into a closed dungeon, killing see thru invis/summoning lb mixed in with mid 50's db is doable, but one mistake (I made one and used my thurg gate potion...fade doesn't work when you have a charm assisting you melee, you still get summoned when it drops.)  And you die in a semi-nasty place or you spend (Thurg potions are at least worth 200pp a pop) enough to net zero your monotary gain.
<br />

<br />
There are some advantages.....
<br />

<br />
You can take, I think, any amount of time to complete it...there is some kind of timer at the top of the window, but it never ran for me.
<br />

<br />
I don't think there is any mechanism to stop an exp group of say, mid 50's from going to DL (hopefully they have a porter) and all taking the same task, then going down and exping in the sentry area and all completing it at the same time? During the last part of my task I had a non-tasked cleric I boxed along (in group) and I still got credit for the last 4 kills.
<br />

<br />
Once you have a list of where the NPC's you talk to are(which are apparently scattered all over the place) you can cut down your time significantly.
<br />

<br />
However, the bottom line, at least at 65, the reward in exp and pp was not worth the run to the old Combine City in DL, much less the next hour or two. Even the story line on this task was not engaging.
<br />

<br />
For myself, I can hope there are better tasks out there and feedback results in a fix. If not, the &quot;puffing of wares&quot; that went on about the task systems is probably out side the rather broad legal limits set for such things.
<br />

<br />
The freakin time was longer than it takes to lfg and do an LDoN for Pete's sake, although, again, I guess you could bust it up and do it in pieces...but there are still quests too numberous to mention that are better on that score than the new tasks.
<br />

<br />
The one unfair thing I have done is condem the system after doing only one.
<br />

<br />
Please though, if you are calling me unfair, have you done several? Go do some then come back and defend it. I'd be interested. The mechanism itself has promise but the implementation is a flat zero on first glance.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
