			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Tasks don't even waste your time<a name="62103"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 15 04 12:28 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Consensus on many popular class-specific boards is that the Task System is generally bad.
<br />

<br />
Limited number of tasks for a given level range, wildly differing level of difficulty (from pretty easy, not counting travel), to impossible (melee solo a room full of dark blues, or get into a zone that requires a key which you don't possess).
<br />

<br />
Find feature doesn't work well in some zones, so tracking is fairly important.  Tracking is also important for zones where you're looking for a less common mob.
<br />

<br />
Those who can travel quickly obviously have an advantage.
<br />

<br />
Tasks generally are not soloable, but can be grouped with similar task hunters.  I foresee task raids forming in zones and completing tasks in much shorter time than SOE expected, and thus raids and possibly even groups being disallowed from completing the same tasks at the same time.
<br />

<br />
Risk/time versus reward is poor.  Duration of task is sometimes long enough that you would have been better off being LFG for 30 minutes until finding an exp group, then spending 1.5hrs exping.
<br />

<br />
I predict a long road of task balancing, with wildly varying results from one patch to the next.  And with reportedly a limited number of tasks for each level range, they'll become stale quickly.  In any event, tasks, if not somewhat randomized (and we know how good (sarcasm) SOE is at doing anything &quot;random&quot;, and making computationally smart decisions on how to provide difficult but doable situation) will become fully listed on websites, as most quests are, and optimizations will be discovered.
<br />

<br />
My take, just from reading many accounts of task experiences is, this system is DOA.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
